      • getName

        public java.lang.String getName()

      • setName

        public void setName(java.lang.String name)
        Name to be set on the control associated with this binding object.
        Name of the control is used for the following purposes among others:
        • To enable differential extensibility.
        • To access control value by name from behavior and extension behavior classes.
        • To do custom validations through extension behavior.
        See Also:
        YRCExtentionBehavior.getFieldValue(String), YRCExtentionBehavior.validateTextField(String, String), YRCExtentionBehavior.validateButtonClick(String), YRCExtentionBehavior.validateComboField(String, String), YRCExtentionBehavior.validateLinkClick(String), YRCExtentionBehavior.validateListField(String, String)

      • getSourceBinding

      • setSourceBinding

        public void setSourceBinding(java.lang.String sourceBinding)
        Source binding of the control. Source binding is used to populate values of the control from an xml model.
        See Also:
        YRCBehavior.setModel(String, Element), YRCExtentionBehavior.setExtentionModel(String, Element)

      • getCurrencyXPath

        public java.lang.String getCurrencyXPath()
        This function returns the currencyXPath. It is supported for non-editable text box, label and table columns. In case of table columns the currencyXPath will be the relative binding i.e. binding after the repeating element.

      • setCurrencyXPath

        public void setCurrencyXPath(java.lang.String currencyXPath)
        currencyXPath is set to indicate that the field is a currency field and currencyXPath will be the xml path from where to get the currency. It is supported for non-editable text box, label and table columns. In case of table columns the currencyXPath will be the relative binding i.e. binding after the repeating element.
